    {
      "title": "Original Mathematics Problem\n\nLet the integer part of \\sqrt{10}-2 be a, and the decimal part be b. Find the value of a-b.\n\n3<\\sqrt{10}<4\n\nSince 1<\\sqrt{10}-2<2 we have\n\na=1,\\ b=(\\sqrt{10}-2)-1=\\sqrt{10}-3\n\\therefore a-b=1-(\\sqrt{10}-3)=4-\\sqrt{10}",
      "heading_level": null,
      "page_id": 2,
      "polygon": [
        [
          150.74609375,
          75.72751558325912
        ],
        [
          291.59765625,
