    {
      "title": "Let the integer part of \\sqrt{111} - 9 be a, and the decimal part be b. Find the value of a - b. 10 < \\sqrt{111} < 11 Since 1 < \\sqrt{111} - 9 < 2, we have a = 1, \\ b = (\\sqrt{111} - 9) - 1 = \\sqrt{111} - 10 \\therefore \\ a - b = 1 - (\\sqrt{111} - 10) = 11 - \\sqrt{111}",
